Here's the XAML and ViewModel setup:

**XAML â€” wrap CollectionView in RefreshView for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <VerticalStackLayout Grid.Column="1" VerticalOptions="Center">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Text="{Binding Description}"
                               FontSize="12" TextColor="Gray" />
                    </VerticalStackLayout>
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel bindings needed:**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    // Pull-to-refresh: reload from API, then set IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        IsRefreshing = false;  // must reset or spinner stays
    }

    // Selection: navigate to detail, then clear selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", CurrentItem }
        });
        CurrentItem = null;  // clear so user can re-select same item
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` â†’ `ObservableCollection<T>` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` â†’ `CurrentItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks selected item |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` â†’ `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires navigation on tap |
| `IsRefreshing` â†’ `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | Controls refresh spinner |
| `Command` on RefreshView â†’ `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |

**Important:** Set `CurrentItem = null` after navigating so the user can re-select the same item. Set `IsRefreshing = false` when the refresh finishes or the spinner won't dismiss. Never use `ViewCell` inside the template â€” use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, or any `View` directly.
